verses.text_plain: Moreover the word of the Lord came unto me, saying,
verses.verse_html: 1Moreover the word of the Lord came unto me, saying,

verses.text_plain: Also, thou son of man, thus saith the Lord God unto the land of Israel; An end, the end is come upon the four corners of the land.
verses.verse_html: 2Also, thou son of man, thus saith the Lord God unto the land of Israel; An end, the end is come upon the four corners of the land.

verses.text_plain: Now is the end come upon thee, and I will send mine anger upon thee, and will judge thee according to thy ways, and will recompense upon thee all thine abominations.
verses.verse_html:
3Now is the end come upon thee, and I will send mine anger upon thee, and will judge thee according to thy ways, and will recompense upon thee all thine abominations. ▼
▼ recompense: Heb. give

tokens.text: upon thee, and I will send

verses.text_plain: And mine eye shall not spare thee, neither will I have pity: but I will recompense thy ways upon thee, and thine abominations shall be in the midst of thee: and ye shall know that I am the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 4And mine eye shall not spare thee, neither will I have pity: but I will recompense thy ways upon thee, and thine abominations shall be in the midst of thee: and ye shall know that I am the Lord.

tokens.text: thee, neither will I have pity
of thee: and ye shall know

verses.text_plain: Thus saith the Lord God; An evil, an only evil, behold, is come.
verses.verse_html: 5Thus saith the Lord God; An evil, an only evil, behold, is come.

verses.text_plain: An end is come, the end is come: it watcheth for thee; behold, it is come.
verses.verse_html:
6An end is come, the end is come: it watcheth for thee; behold, it is come. ▼
▼ watcheth for: Heb. awaketh against

tokens.text: for thee; behold, it is come

footnotes.body_html: ▼ watcheth for: Heb. awaketh against

verses.text_plain: The morning is come unto thee, O thou that dwellest in the land: the time is come, the day of trouble is near, and not the sounding again of the mountains.
verses.verse_html:
7The morning is come unto thee, O thou that dwellest in the land: the time is come, the day of trouble is near, and not the sounding again of the mountains. ▼
▼ sounding…: or, echo

tokens.text: unto thee, O thou that dwellest

verses.text_plain: Now will I shortly pour out my fury upon thee, and accomplish mine anger upon thee: and I will judge thee according to thy ways, and will recompense thee for all thine abominations.
verses.verse_html: 8Now will I shortly pour out my fury upon thee, and accomplish mine anger upon thee: and I will judge thee according to thy ways, and will recompense thee for all thine abominations.

tokens.text: upon thee: and I will judge

verses.text_plain: And mine eye shall not spare, neither will I have pity: I will recompense thee according to thy ways and thine abominations that are in the midst of thee; and ye shall know that I am the Lord that smiteth.
verses.verse_html:
9And mine eye shall not spare, neither will I have pity: I will recompense thee according to thy ways and thine abominations that are in the midst of thee; and ye shall know that I am the Lord that smiteth. ▼
▼ thee according: Heb. upon thee, etc

tokens.text: of thee; and ye shall know

footnotes.body_text: ▼ thee according: Heb. upon thee, etc
footnotes.body_html: ▼ thee according: Heb. upon thee, etc

verses.text_plain: Behold the day, behold, it is come: the morning is gone forth; the rod hath blossomed, pride hath budded.
verses.verse_html: 10Behold the day, behold, it is come: the morning is gone forth; the rod hath blossomed, pride hath budded.

verses.text_plain: Violence is risen up into a rod of wickedness: none of them shall remain, nor of their multitude, nor of any of theirs: neither shall there be wailing for them.
verses.verse_html:
11Violence is risen up into a rod of wickedness: none of them shall remain, nor of their multitude, nor of any of theirs: neither shall there be wailing for them. ▼
▼ theirs: or, their tumultuous persons: Heb. tumult

footnotes.body_text: ▼ theirs: or, their tumultuous persons: Heb. tumult
footnotes.body_html: ▼ theirs: or, their tumultuous persons: Heb. tumult

verses.text_plain: The time is come, the day draweth near: let not the buyer rejoice, nor the seller mourn: for wrath is upon all the multitude thereof.
verses.verse_html: 12The time is come, the day draweth near: let not the buyer rejoice, nor the seller mourn: for wrath is upon all the multitude thereof.

verses.text_plain: For the seller shall not return to that which is sold, although they were yet alive: for the vision is touching the whole multitude thereof, which shall not return; neither shall any strengthen himself in the iniquity of his life.
verses.verse_html:
13For the seller shall not return to that which is sold, although they were yet alive: for the vision is touching the whole multitude thereof, which shall not return; neither shall any strengthen himself in the iniquity of his life. ▼
▼ although they…: Heb. though their life were yet among the living
 , ▼
▼ in the…: or, whose life is in his iniquity
 , ▼
▼ the iniquity: Heb. his iniquity

footnotes.body_text: ▼ although they…: Heb. though their life were yet among the living
footnotes.body_html: ▼ although they…: Heb. though their life were yet among the living

footnotes.body_html: ▼ in the…: or, whose life is in his iniquity
▼ the iniquity: Heb. his iniquity

verses.text_plain: They have blown the trumpet, even to make all ready; but none goeth to the battle: for my wrath is upon all the multitude thereof.
verses.verse_html: 14They have blown the trumpet, even to make all ready; but none goeth to the battle: for my wrath is upon all the multitude thereof.

verses.text_plain: The sword is without, and the pestilence and the famine within: he that is in the field shall die with the sword; and he that is in the city, famine and pestilence shall devour him.
verses.verse_html: 15The sword is without, and the pestilence and the famine within: he that is in the field shall die with the sword; and he that is in the city, famine and pestilence shall devour him.

verses.text_plain: But they that escape of them shall escape, and shall be on the mountains like doves of the valleys, all of them mourning, every one for his iniquity.
verses.verse_html: 16But they that escape of them shall escape, and shall be on the mountains like doves of the valleys, all of them mourning, every one for his iniquity.

tokens.text: and shall be on the mountains

verses.text_plain: All hands shall be feeble, and all knees shall be weak as water.
verses.verse_html:
17All hands shall be feeble, and all knees shall be weak as water. ▼
▼ be weak…: Heb. go into water

footnotes.body_text: ▼ be weak…: Heb. go into water
footnotes.body_html: ▼ be weak…: Heb. go into water

verses.text_plain: They shall also gird themselves with sackcloth, and horror shall cover them; and shame shall be upon all faces, and baldness upon all their heads.
verses.verse_html: 18They shall also gird themselves with sackcloth, and horror shall cover them; and shame shall be upon all faces, and baldness upon all their heads.

verses.text_plain: They shall cast their silver in the streets, and their gold shall be removed: their silver and their gold shall not be able to deliver them in the day of the wrath of the Lord: they shall not satisfy their souls, neither fill their bowels: because it is the stumblingblock of their iniquity.
verses.verse_html:
19They shall cast their silver in the streets, and their gold shall be removed: their silver and their gold shall not be able to deliver them in the day of the wrath of the Lord: they shall not satisfy their souls, neither fill their bowels: because it is the stumblingblock of their iniquity. ▼
▼ removed: Heb. for a separation, or, uncleanness
 , ▼
▼ it is…: or, their iniquity is their stumblingblock

footnotes.body_text: ▼ removed: Heb. for a separation, or, uncleanness
footnotes.body_html: ▼ removed: Heb. for a separation, or, uncleanness

footnotes.body_text: ▼ it is…: or, their iniquity is their stumblingblock
footnotes.body_html: ▼ it is…: or, their iniquity is their stumblingblock

verses.text_plain: As for the beauty of his ornament, he set it in majesty: but they made the images of their abominations and of their detestable things therein: therefore have I set it far from them.
verses.verse_html:
20As for the beauty of his ornament, he set it in majesty: but they made the images of their abominations and of their detestable things therein: therefore have I set it far from them. ▼
▼ set it far…: or, made it unto them an unclean thing

footnotes.body_text: ▼ set it far…: or, made it unto them an unclean thing
footnotes.body_html: ▼ set it far…: or, made it unto them an unclean thing

verses.text_plain: And I will give it into the hands of the strangers for a prey, and to the wicked of the earth for a spoil; and they shall pollute it.
verses.verse_html: 21And I will give it into the hands of the strangers for a prey, and to the wicked of the earth for a spoil; and they shall pollute it.

verses.text_plain: My face will I turn also from them, and they shall pollute my secret place: for the robbers shall enter into it, and defile it.
verses.verse_html:
22My face will I turn also from them, and they shall pollute my secret place: for the robbers shall enter into it, and defile it. ▼
▼ robbers: or, burglers

tokens.text: also from them, and they shall pollute

verses.text_plain: Make a chain: for the land is full of bloody crimes, and the city is full of violence.
verses.verse_html: 23Make a chain: for the land is full of bloody crimes, and the city is full of violence.

verses.text_plain: Wherefore I will bring the worst of the heathen, and they shall possess their houses: I will also make the pomp of the strong to cease; and their holy places shall be defiled.
verses.verse_html:
24Wherefore I will bring the worst of the heathen, and they shall possess their houses: I will also make the pomp of the strong to cease; and their holy places shall be defiled. ▼
▼ their holy…: or, they shall inherit their holy places

tokens.text: I will also make the pomp

footnotes.body_text: ▼ their holy…: or, they shall inherit their holy places
footnotes.body_html: ▼ their holy…: or, they shall inherit their holy places

verses.text_plain: Destruction cometh; and they shall seek peace, and there shall be none.
verses.verse_html:
25Destruction cometh; and they shall seek peace, and there shall be none. ▼
▼ Destruction: Heb. Cutting off

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Destruction: Heb. Cutting off

verses.text_plain: Mischief shall come upon mischief, and rumour shall be upon rumour; then shall they seek a vision of the prophet; but the law shall perish from the priest, and counsel from the ancients.
verses.verse_html: 26Mischief shall come upon mischief, and rumour shall be upon rumour; then shall they seek a vision of the prophet; but the law shall perish from the priest, and counsel from the ancients.

verses.text_plain: The king shall mourn, and the prince shall be clothed with desolation, and the hands of the people of the land shall be troubled: I will do unto them after their way, and according to their deserts will I judge them; and they shall know that I am the Lord.
verses.verse_html:
27The king shall mourn, and the prince shall be clothed with desolation, and the hands of the people of the land shall be troubled: I will do unto them after their way, and according to their deserts will I judge them; and they shall know that I am the Lord. ▼
▼ according…: Heb. with their judgments

footnotes.body_html: ▼ according…: Heb. with their judgments
